sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Cmd.EXE Missing Space Characters Execution Anomaly
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects Windows command lines that miss a space before or after the /c flag when running a command using the cmd.exe.
This could be a sign of obfuscation of a fat finger problem (typo by the developer).
Detects the execution of whoami, which is often used by attackers after exploitation / privilege escalation
Local accounts, System Owner/User discovery using operating systems utilities

attributes.magic: PE32+ executable (console) x86-64, for MS Windows

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.
